Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Cut the @lemon{1} into wedges. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g} and garlic, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a squeeze of lemon juice from a lemon wedge and allow to evaporate, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{20%g} and @boiled water{550%ml} into the rice pan.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pop the sliced pepper onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{14-16%minutes}.

When ready, remove the risotto from the oven and stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}.

> Add less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the roasted pepper and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Mix until combined.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Taste and season with more @salt{}, @pepper{} and @lemon juice{} if needed.

Share the risotto between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and @crispy onions{1%sachet}, then serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!